Customized Deal App

Back end 

Learn `rails generate model` from: http://railsguides.net/advanced-rails-model-generators/

- Database   (data source: Staples.com)
  a. user (based on tutorial example)
  b. product (id, staples_pid, msrp, price)
    rails generate model product staples_pid:string:index:uniq{6} 'msrp:decimal{10,2}' 'price:decimal{10,2}'
  c. alert (id, product_id, user_id, expectation)
    rails generate model alert user:references product:references 'expectation:decimal{10,2}'
  d. price history (product_id, update_time, price)
    rails generate model history user:references product:references 'msrp:decimal{10,2}'



- Automatically Catch Change

Front end

Page 1: Login -- tutorial  (banner, user_id, password, register, forget id/pwd, login)

Page 2: 

Create New Item: search box + Add
Index Existing Items (Product/MSRP/Current Price)
Update target price
Delete existing item


